<font color="#FF0000">MTF'S 12 DAYS OF CHRISTMAS</font><br>
<tt>Thu Dec 25 15:10:22 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
MTFĺs Twelve days of Christmas<br><br>
Dear Cook,<br><br>
I want to thank you for the gifts you have send, <br>
On the first day, <br>
The partridge and the pear tree -- how thoughtful! <br>
On the Second Day <br>
Two turtle doves. Beautiful, but how do I stop them from cooing?<br>
Third day<br>
Three more birds! Little French hens like we had in Viet Nam, how thoughtful, but they donĺt get along with the two turtle doves and the partridge.<br>
All of them are messing all over the place, but  I guess they are a gift from you and I appreciate it. <br>
Fourth Day<br>
Ha, ha, ha, these ones are a joke, right? Four calling birds? Now that gives me a total of ten birds in our home, wife does not like pets at all and the racket is also getting to be too much. They don't call them &quot;calling birds&quot; for nothing, you know. They set off the French hens, and now the turtle doves are cooing around the clock. The partridge looks sick.<br>
Five Day <br>
Five golden rings! They are precious, what a lovely gift. I guess I can put up with the feathers and the seeds on my carpet or the mess the French hens are making. Naturally you won't want to send me any more gifts. But I shall always treasure your thoughtfulness and now, know how much you care in giving me the five golden rings. <br>
Sixth Day <br>
Not funny, Cook. Your six geese a-laying have nearly ruined my den, no one will eat the eggs. <br>
Now that you've had your little joke, I hope you'll come and take them off my hands before Toon Sgt and my other Vietnam buddies I have invited over for a New Years celebration get here.<br>
Seventh Day <br>
The wife wants those seven swans out of our bathtub. It is was bad enough to have 16 birds in our home, but the swans are splashing water all over the bathroom and it's turning the goose, chickens, doves, and the partridge poop into a stinking mess. The carpet is ruined. My daughter is threatening to call Animal Control and I'm going to be embarrassed about the mess. Get over here and help me clean out this mess immediately. <br>
Eighth Day<br>
I can hardly write this because of the uproar from your eight maids a-milking and their stinkin' cows. All the birds are covered with cow poop. The maids donĺt speak English and they are always quarreling among themselves and I barely have enough money to buy hay. I don't know where you got these women, I think they are illegal, one of them is chasing the French hens with a hatchet. So, if they aren't gone by tomorrow, I'm calling Art and Bob. I know, Gary would have shot them all if he wasnĺt out of town, Iĺll call him. What are you trying to prove anyway? <br>
Nine Day<br>
Cook, You've gone too far! Nine ladies dancing would be bad enough, but these so-called dancing ladies when they're not dancing, are tripping all over the place breaking things, they're fighting with the milkmaids, They are all fat and eating everything in the place. <br>
You can call it dancing if you want, but they'd get arrested in most nightclubs. It's disgusting. Three of them have been hurt slipping in the cow poop and one of them the heaviest in the bunch likes to run around naked all day long. I can't stand it another day; the chaos is driving me crazy. <br>
Tenth Day<br>
You're a dead man, Cook! <br>
Ten lords a-leaping are now jumping all over the milkmaids and the ladies you stupidly sent, not to mention jumping over each other. Two of the milkmaids have locked themselves in the bathroom in spite of the geese and swans and the racket and their slimy droppings. Have you ever seen lords a-leaping? They're gross! If you have any heart at all, You and little PePe would come get them out of here. With all the acid from all the poop on the floor and the stink in the house the golden rings have turned green. I called the police but they laughed at me. I don't know where to turn. <br><br>
Eleventh Day<br>
I suppose you'll be happy to know that when the eleven pipers piped their way into the house today they got everyone all ruffled up. First the two turtle doves started cooing, the French hens began to squawk, the calling birds started calling, the six geese squealing , the swans splashing, the maids went to milking, The ladies went to dancing and the leaping lordĺs started leaping. It all turned out more then the poor partridge, that was still sick, could take and he died in all that commotion.<br><br>
Twelve Day<br>
Dear Mr. Cook:<br>
I am writing this on behalf of my client, Mustang Two Four, who is now under psychiatric care at Chelsea Medical Center. Apparently your gift of twelve drummers drumming proved to be more than he could bear. A suit has been filed charging you with $900,000 in damages to his house and many other persons, including an Animal Control officer who would only say that his name was LBW and  was accidentally wounded in the mortar barraged.<br><br>
On the twelve day after your presents begin to arrive, My clients closest of friends, Tom, Bob, Toon Sgt, Gary, Pee Pee , Art, Class Lass and the Corpsmen were all coming over to help him get rid of the stuff youĺve been sending.<br>
 <br>
Just as they approached my clients perimeters wire, the twelve drummers sounded off and all heck broke loose. <br><br>
All of my clients friends being former Vietnam veterans hit the dirt. Tom thinking it was the enemy, cried out, IN-COMING! and Gary opened fire with the M-60. Class Lass became stuck in heavy cow poop and is suing you separately on that account. <br><br>
During the initial fire fight the swans and the geese were startled and began to make a racked in the upstairs bathroom. Pee Pee figuring it was the enemy hiding there used his tunnel rat experience to sneak up the chimney and then tossed two grenades in. About this time Artillery Art fired off six beehive rounds from his mortar tubes all around the perimeter. Silent Warrior had already jumped into his fighter plane and came in low, just in time to take out nine of the enemy as they tried went leaping into a nearby tree line.<br><br>
Unfortunately when all this started the noise also stampeded the cows. They ran through the house, just as the grenades explosion above them ripped the bath tub from the wall and all the bird poop mess came crashing through the floor of the upper bathroom and flooded the whole downstairs. The Animal Control officer accompanying the Vietnam veterans slipped on cow poop and accidentally shot a milking maid with his tranquilizer gun. <br>
Doc Dell treated her at the scene but in examining one of the dancing ladies he found her to be pregnant from either one of the leaping lords or a one of the Pipers. The milkmaids all dropped their milk containers and so milk was splattered all over the place. The geese and swans tried to fly out the upstairs windows but Gary shot them all dead as they came flying out. The four calling birds had all of their feathers plucked out by the exploding beehive round and the poor little things are all huddled over in the corner of the house looking like little rubber chickens. <br><br>
My client at about this time was somehow also attacked by the a gay leaping lord who had stayed behind.<br>
Because of all this my client became so upset that he strangled the turtle doves. They were so sweet, but he just couldn't take any more! <br>
The house has been totally destroyed, The stench is unbearable. The air is filled with feathers, poop, sour milk, and we canĺt pry the pipers from off the pear tree.<br><br>
Signed <br>
Your avowed enemy, MTF<br><br>
Witnessed by <br>
John C. Ratliff, Attorney at Law<br><br>

